Skypay Banking System

📌 Project Overview

Skypay is a simple banking system that allows users to manage their bank accounts by performing operations such as depositing, withdrawing, and viewing their transaction history. The system follows an Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) approach with Java and uses Lombok for reducing boilerplate code.

🛠️ Tech Stack

Java (JDK 17+)

Lombok (for reducing boilerplate code)

Maven (for dependency management)

🚀 Features

Deposit money into an account 💰

Withdraw money from an account 🏦

View transaction history 📄

Display an interactive menu for user actions 🎛️

Exception handling for invalid transactions ❌

📂 Project Structure

Skypay
│── src
│   ├── main
│   │   ├── java
│   │   │   ├── com.skypay
│   │   │   │   ├── controller      # Handles user interactions
│   │   │   │   ├── model           # Contains domain models (Account, Transaction)
│   │   │   │   ├── service         # Defines business logic
│   │   │   │   ├── service.impl    # Implements service logic
│   │   │   │   ├── exception       # Custom exception handling
│   │   │   ├── Main.java           # Entry point of the application
│   ├── test                        # Unit tests (if implemented)

🔧 Installation & Setup

Prerequisites

Install Java 8+

Install Maven

Steps to Run the Project

Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/mouadHILLALI/SkyPay-Tech-Test

Navigate to the project directory:

cd skypay

Compile and run the project:

mvn clean compile
mvn package
java -jar target/demo-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar

📖 How to Use

Run the application.

Choose an operation from the menu:

1. Deposit: Enter an amount to deposit into your account.

2. Withdraw: Enter an amount to withdraw (if sufficient balance is available).

3. Print Statement: View all past transactions.

4. Exit: Close the application.

⚠️ Exception Handling

The system handles the following exceptions:

InvalidDepositAmountException: When a user tries to deposit a negative or zero amount.

InvalidWithdrawAmountException: When a user tries to withdraw a negative or zero amount.

InsufficientBalanceException: When a user attempts to withdraw more than the available balance.

